S.description: base load demand not counting child objects, copied from Pd,Qd by default (MVA)

type.description: bus type (1 = PQ, 2 = PV, 3 = ref, 4 = isolated)

lam_P.description: Lagrange multiplier on real power mismatch (u/MW)

lam_Q.description: Lagrange multiplier on reactive power mismatch (u/MVAr)

mu_Vmax.description: Kuhn-Tucker multiplier on upper voltage limit (u/p.u.)

mu_Vmin.description: Kuhn-Tucker multiplier on lower voltage limit (u/p.u.)

status.description: initial branch status, 1 - in service, 0 - out of service

mBase.description: total MVA base of machine, defaults to baseMVA

Pc1.description: lower real power output of PQ capability curve (MW)

Pc2.description: upper real power output of PQ capability curve (MW)

Qc1min.description: minimum reactive power output at Pc1 (MVAr)

Qc1max.description: maximum reactive power output at Pc1 (MVAr)

Qc2min.description: minimum reactive power output at Pc2 (MVAr)

Qc2max.description: maximum reactive power output at Pc2 (MVAr)

ramp_q.description: ramp rate for reactive power (2 sec timescale) (MVAr/min)

mu_Pmax.description: Kuhn-Tucker multiplier on upper Pg limit (p.u./MW)

mu_Pmin.description: Kuhn-Tucker multiplier on lower Pg limit (p.u./MW)

mu_Qmax.description: Kuhn-Tucker multiplier on upper Qg limit (p.u./MVAr)

mu_Qmin.description: Kuhn-Tucker multiplier on lower Qg limit (p.u./MVAr)

response.description: curtailment response as fractional load reduction

city.description: City in which powerplant is located

state.description: State in which powerplant is located

zipcode.description: Zipcode in which powerplant is located

country.description: Country in which powerplant is located

point.description: Enable access to point specified as object <name>:<property>

record.description: Enable recording of point to historian

phase_shift.description: transformer phase shift (deg) - use 30 for DY or YD transformers

file.description: file from which to read values

loop.description: number of time to loop the player

file.description: file in which to record data

filetype.description: file type to use when storing data

limit.description: limit on number of rows to record (0=none)

flush.description: row flush mode (-1=when full, 0=every row, >0=interval in seconds)

header_units.description: header option for output of units

line_units.description: inline option for output of units

file.description: file in which to record data

filetype.description: file type to use when storing data

limit.description: limit on number of rows to record (0=none)

filename.description: the name of the file to write

filetype.description: the format to output a histogram in

group.description: the GridLAB-D group expression to use for this histogram

bins.description: the specific bin values to use

min.description: the minimum value of the auto-sized bins to use

max.description: the maximum value of the auto-sized bins to use

samplerate.description: the rate at which samples are read

countrate.description: the reate at which bins are counted and written

bin_count.description: the number of auto-sized bins to use

limit.description: the number of samples to write

flush_interval.description: file flush interval (0 never, negative on samples)

strict.description: causes the group_recorder to stop the simulation should there be a problem opening or writing with the group_recorder

print_units.description: flag to append units to each written value, if applicable

limit.description: the maximum number of lines to write to the file

format.description: determines whether output timestamp is formatted to be formatted as human-readable (default) or epoch

complex_part.description: the complex part to record if complex properties are gathered

virtual_substation.description: name of the substation node to monitor for reverse flow violation

flush_interval.description: file flush interval (0 never, negative on samples)

strict.description: causes the violation_recorder to stop the simulation should there be a problem opening or writing with the violation_recorder

echo.description: causes the violation_recorder to echo messages to the screen

limit.description: the maximum number of lines to write to the file

violation_delay.description: the number of seconds to skip before recording violations

violation_flag.description: bit set for determining which violations to check

interval.description: Interval at which the metrics_collector output is stored in JSON format

filename.description: the JSON formatted output file name

interval.description: Interval at which the metrics_collector_writer output is stored in JSON format
